# Testing Discipline

- **Never delete tests** without explicit product owner direction. When a test fails, fix it—don't remove or skip it.

- **Fix tests within intended behavior.** Maintain the feature contract; don't alter functionality merely to satisfy a test.

- **Escalate when blocked.** If you cannot make a test pass without altering functionality, surface the issue with context instead of muting or deleting the test.
